type_definition: The subject is a subtype of the object.
The predicate is a constituent element of the subject (either integral or proper).
type_example: Cue specification is a part of memory retrieval.

type_definition: The two terms are transitively synonomous.
type_example: Declarative memory is a synonym of explicit memory..

type_definition: The subject is preceded temporally by the predicate.
The subject task is derivative of the predicate task.
type_example: Masked lexical decision task derives from lexical decision task.

type_definition: The concept can be measured by the task:contrast.
type_example: Conflict detection is measured by the contrast of incongruent - congruent trials in the color-word stroop task
